reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dent easily, but dense
reviews.reviewText: They are very dense, no sculpting. Pretty colors are nice when I want to use them for different things and need to remember which is which. Color coding makes that easy. Other brands are all pink or shades of pink, and I have to store the sponges in certain places to know which is for which product. It is not like you can write on them without it looking gross. I use many sponges at once to apply only one product each so there is no cross-contamination, and I clean them regularly with soap and water and replace them regularly. I would not travel with these because I put them into a drawer, and they got creases from being pressed next to the others for only a few days. Store them in the container until you are ready to use them. The softer ones have more give but absorb more makeup, which is wasteful. Look at the photo where I am squishing the sponge. It is so dense that it won't squish down all the way but still effectively and smoothly applies makeup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome & Cheap Makeup Sponges
reviews.reviewText: Guys, let me spill the tea on these makeup sponges – they're seriously awesome and dirt cheap!First off, they're soft and bouncy, blending makeup like a dream. Whether it's foundation, blush, or concealer, these sponges got you covered, literally!And guess what? They come in different shapes and sizes, perfect for getting into every nook and cranny of your face.Now, let's talk about the price tag – it's a steal! Just a little soap and water, and they're good to go for round two.Whether you're a makeup newbie or a pro, these sponges are a game-changer. Trust me, you won't regret adding them to your makeup stash!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The BEST generic BeautyBlender!
reviews.reviewText: These are seriously the BEST generic Beauty Blender!! Why anyone would pay $20 for a name-brand Beauty Blender when there’s excellent dupes like these is beyond my realm of comprehension. These are just as soft, bouncy, and absorbent (but not overly so, as to waste product) as the name brand. And they cost a little over $1 a piece, as compared to the AT LEAST $20 price tag on the name brand Beauty Blenders! So this is a total no-brainer! I find washing my BB’s a pain in the a$$, even with alcohol, so @ this price, they’re pretty much disposable. This is the 4th or 5th package of these i’ve purchased, and i hope they never stop making them @ this cost. Coz i’ll buy this brand til the end of time, if they let me!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price, but not a dupe
reviews.reviewText: I use these quite a bit. There is a difference between them and the higher end, sponges but not enough to justify paying a higher higher price. In my opinion, unless you’re doing something very special and you want to really apply your make up flawlessly. They are easy to wash, but I do notice that some of them have fallen apart quicker than the others. I don’t know if it has to do with color or a different lot in the same bag. Definitely worth buying when you want to cut corners on your budget..

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars They work, but something is off with these
reviews.reviewText: I've been using these for a couple months and they work, but they are a little weird, and each behaves a little differently. They do swell in size, so it at least has that going for it. They are very dense as well - not sure if that's a cause of some of the below issues.I think some of them might be retaining moisture or something? I had one that didn't fully dry for over 3 days (even after leaving it on my car's dashboard in the sun), at which point I just threw it out because nothing should be wet for that long.Another one didn't clean as fully as the previous one, which is so strange since they are supposed to be the same product.I'm on my 3rd or 4th from the pack right now and I will go with a different brand next time around.

These are cheaper than beauty blender and do the job well. It might not be as soft as beauty blender (pretty close tho) but it gives the same result with a fraction of the price. As a makeup artist, I tried different brands but these are the softest and give best result out of all dupes. Whenever I do makeup for a bride, I always give it to the bride for her personal use after.I use it for personal use as well but the only downside is, it breaks down faster than beauty blender. That is actually not an issue, because it is so affordable, I can toss it out more often therefore making it more hygienic.

Éponges efficaces pour le fond de teint liquide et l’anti cernes liquide. Un peu moins pour le blush en crème pour moi. Elles sont plus rigides que celles de la marque très connue (testée) et le resultat final après avoir estompé est meilleur. Le teint se fond vraiment bien pareil pour l’anti cernes. Elles n’absorbent pas plus que l’éponge de la marque très connue. Elles semblent être beaucoup plus solides (moins de risque de déchirures). Elles gonflent presque jusqu’à doubler de leur volume initial. Donc si vous cherchez à être précise, je vous conseille d’utiliser la pointe de l’éponge ou carrément d’acheter une éponge plus petite. Attention, comme indiqué dans la notice, il faut bien les laver avant utilisation car odeurs « chimiques » et colorants (?? Qui ne colorent plus après). Je recommande ce produit pour son efficacité à prix attractif.

Arrivage rapide (attention elles sont emballées en longueur donc si vous avez une petite boite aux lettres, ça peut ne pas rentrer).Elles sont top. Absorbance classique comme avec celles du commerce donc on perd un peu de matière au début. J'aime leur taille qui permet une bonne prise en mais et d'avoir de quoi étaler.Lavage simple et rapide

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2 years strong - I can’t recommend these enough!
reviews.reviewText: I first purchased these in 2020, then again in 2022 before I moved countries and was stocking up on new things. For the price, you absolutely cannot go wrong! They’ve lasted me perfectly since I last purchased them. I usually wash mine every few times I use them because I personally don’t like the buildup of makeup, and they’re so easy to wash. Once damp they grow to a perfect size to apply my foundation, and I even sometimes use a dry one as a powder puff and it definitely does the trick. They apply everything smoothly and evenly, and keep their shape well. Thought it was about time I gave these a review! Cannot recommend enough!
